oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: UNICEF tour - New Zealand - 1972 - part 10
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Part ten of a 1972 UNICEF fundraiser tour performance in New Zealand. Featuring Tex Ritter (host/performer), Wanda Jackson (performer), and Leroy Van Dyke (performer).
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Wanda Jackson; Leroy Van Dyke
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00) Silver Threads And Golden Needles (Wanda Jackson) (incomplete) -- (00:36) In The Middle Of A Heartache (Wanda Jackson) -- (02:20) Jackson thanks the audience and introduces the next tune -- (04:21) Right Or Wrong (Wanda Jackson) -- (06:12) Jackson thanks the audience and attempts to start a new song, but then decides to a different one -- (07:18) If I Had A Hammer (Wanda Jackson) -- (12:20) Jackson thanks the audience -- (12:47) I Betcha My Heart I Love You (Wanda Jackson) -- (14:24) Jackson thanks the band and the audience, who ask for an encore -- Jackson thanks the audience again and jokes with them -- (16:16) Cowboy Yodel (Wanda Jackson) -- (18:12) Jackson thanks the audience and talks about her faith in Jesus -- (19:30) The King Is Coming (Wanda Jackson) -- (22:56) Ritter thanks and praises Jackson -- (24:35) Ritter introduces Leroy Van Dyke -- (25:43) Walk On By (Leroy Van Dyke auctioneer) -- (27:09) Walk On By (Leroy Van Dyke)
